-- Nigeria's foreign reserves rise to $39.6 bln on Aug 26
-- 
-- Fri Aug 29, 2014 07:42AM EDT
-- None



LAGOS, Aug 29 (Reuters) - Nigeria's foreign reserves <NGFXR=ECI> rose to $39.62 billion on Aug. 26, up 1.43 percent from $39.06 billion a month previously, central bank data showed on Friday, as offshore inflows into the local bond market helped the naira currency stabilise.

